
[1]guinea-hen

   GUIN'EA-HEN, n. The Numida meleagris, a fowl of the gallinaceous order,
   a native of Africa. It is larger than the common domestic hen, and has
   a kind of colored fleshy horn on each side of the head. Its color is a
   dark gray, beautifully variegated with small white spots.
